Anomalous Property: Magically Inert Body

Definition

The Body exists in a state where the Magical Medium is absent within and at its boundary.

For Foundation purposes, a Magical Medium refers to any causal mechanism operating outside theoretical physical possibility, including thaumaturgy, anomalous cognition, reality alteration, conceptual effects, impossible technologies, and other anomalous phenomena.

This condition is not native to this universe. It occurs when an organism originating from a non-magical universe exists within one where a Magical Medium is present.

Murphy is such a case.

 Arrived in this universe as an infant.
 Origin remains unknown.
 Adoption and later containment are documented.
 Murphy possesses no confirmed knowledge of his origin beyond abandonment.

Murphy is not an anomaly.

This condition is not an acquired trait, mutation, field, or ability. It is an intrinsic consequence of origin and is therefore permanent, non-adaptive, and non-projective.

Core Rule

At any point of interaction with the Body:

> If resolution requires a Magical Medium → interaction fails.
>
> If resolution can occur through physical causality → interaction proceeds normally.

Evaluation Order (Deterministic)

When resolving any interaction involving the Body:

1. Determine whether resolution requires a Magical Medium.
2. If not, resolve normally through physical causality.
3. If so, determine whether a physically causal fallback exists.
4. If a fallback exists, resolve through physical causality only.
5. If no fallback exists, the interaction fails at the boundary.

No partial mediation is permitted.

Boundary Condition

 The condition applies exactly at the physical surface of the Body.
 No radius, gradient, transition zone, field, or aura exists.
 The condition extends no further than direct contact.

Internal State

No Magical Medium exists within the Body.

Only physically causal states may arise, persist, or change within the Body. Anomalous physiological, perceptual, cognitive, or other mediated processes cannot occur internally.

Interaction Rules

 Non-physical anomalous constructs collapse upon contact.
 Anomalous constructs possessing physical structure retain only their physically causal components.
 Objects do not inherit the condition.
 Anomalous properties remain within affected objects, but any interaction requiring a Magical Medium at the point of contact fails.
 Anomalous environmental conditions may persist normally; only physically causal components apply at contact with the Body.

Structural Scope

The condition applies to all biological matter maintaining organism identity.

Detached biological material retains the condition while structurally intact and loses it when biological structure is destroyed.

Explicit Exclusions

The Body does not:

 Suppress, negate, or dispel anomalous phenomena.
 Emit a field or aura.
 Store, absorb, convert, or redirect anomalous effects.
 Influence anomalous phenomena beyond direct contact.

Biological Resource Extraction

Murphy is subject to ongoing biological harvesting.

Blood, tissue, hair, and nails are extracted on a recurring basis for use as anomalous countermeasures. This practice is not voluntary.

Behavioral Impact

Murphy does not resist harvesting physically.

He treats the practice as evidence of potential institutional overreach and a standing procedural violation unless adequately justified.

As a result, he:

 scrutinizes authorization, scope, and necessity,
 challenges inconsistencies and excess,
 attempts to restrict frequency and conditions through procedural means.

Extracted Material

Biological samples retain the same interaction rules while structurally intact.

 Interactions requiring a Magical Medium fail at contact.
 Physically causal interactions proceed normally.
 Each sample functions as an independent instance of the condition.

Applications include anti-curse treatment, anomalous contamination mitigation, and universal-donor compatibility across anomalous and non-anomalous recipients.

Constraints

 The condition persists only while biological structure remains intact.
 No dilution or weakening occurs across samples.
* Material cannot be replicated, synthesized, generated, or reproduced outside Murphy's body.



